# <%= it.displayName %>

<%= it.description %>

Generated by [MCP Tool Generator](https://github.com/example/mcp-tool-generator) using `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk@<%= it.MCP_SDK_VERSION %>`.

## Quick start

```bash
pnpm install
cp .env.example .env
pnpm dev
```

The MCP server starts on port <%= it.port %> and exposes the `<%= it.mcpEndpoint %>` endpoint.

## Connecting to Claude Desktop

Add to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "url": "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"
    }
  }
}
```

## Connecting to Claude Code

```bash
claude mcp add --transport http <%= it.serverName %> http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>
```

## Connecting to Cursor

Add to your Cursor MCP config:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "url": "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"
    }
  }
}
```

